Continuing our partnership with Duetti as it secures $200M to grow its art=
ist-first acquisition platform.

We=E2=80=99re delighted to share that during H1 2025=2C Duetti closed a $2=
00M debt facility=2C comprising a $150M bank facility and a $50M tactical=
 side facility from Viola Credit=2C with capacity rights of up to $100M.

This financing will support Duetti=E2=80=99s growing acquisition volumes a=
nd enable the company to expand beyond master rights into publishing right=
s and royalty streams.
Read More (https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/duetti-expands-financi=
al-offerings-for-independent-music-creators-with-royalty-and-publishing-de=
als-announces-200m-in-new-funding-302390310.html)

PayZen secures $200M debt facility from Viola Credit alongside $32M

equity raise in Series B

We=E2=80=99re proud to continue our long-standing partnership with PayZen=
=2C providing a new $200M credit warehouse to support the company=E2=80=99=
s next phase of growth. This facility will enable PayZen to expand its hea=
lthcare affordability solutions and scale its AI-driven Care Card offering=
 across the U.S.
Read More (https://techcrunch.com/2024/08/13/payzen-secures-23m-series-b-l=
ed-by-nea-and-200m-in-debt-to-expand-care-now-pay-later-offering/)

Lendbuzz closes $266M securitization=2C its second ABS deal of 2025=2C bri=
nging total issuance to over $2.1B

Our long-standing platform partner and leading auto lender Lendbuzz closed=
 a new $266M financing round backed by a pool of auto loans. This marks it=
s second deal of 2025=2C following a $262M transaction in January=2C bring=
ing total capital raised through these programs to over $2.1B to date.
Read More (https://www.autoremarketing.com/autofinjournal/lendbuzz-complet=
es-second-securitization-of-the-year-topping-260m/)

OatFi raises $24M Series A led by White Star to build the modern credit ne=
twork for B2B payments

We=E2=80=99re excited to see OatFi=2C a leading B2B payments infrastructur=
e fintech=2C raise $24M in its Series A round led by White Star Capital=2C=
 with participation from existing investors Portage and QED.

OatFi enables B2B payment platforms to embed working capital and financing=
 solutions directly into AP=2C AR=2C and charge card workflows via API=2C=
 giving SMBs access to credit at the point of transaction.
Read More (https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20250603492242/en/OatFi-=
Raises-%2424M-to-Build-the-Modern-Credit-Network-for-B2B-Payments)

Read More (https://www.getbalance.com/post/alibaba-pay-later-for-business/=
)

Big News! Balance announced its exciting partnership with Alibaba.com to l=
aunch =E2=80=9CPay Later for Business=2C=E2=80=9D giving U.S. SMEs within=
 Alibaba=E2=80=99s B2B network instant=2C embedded financing powered by Ba=
lance.

Wagestream Secures =C2=A3300M Debt Facility to Accelerate Expansion into L=
ending

We=E2=80=99re proud to back Wagestream as it continues to expand its missi=
on of improving employee financial well-being. The new =C2=A3300M debt fac=
ility will fuel the company=E2=80=99s growth into lending=2C complementing=
 its existing services=2C which include earned wage access=2C budgeting=2C=
 financial coaching=2C and savings tools.
Read More (https://www.uktech.news/fintech/wagestream-secures-300m-debt-fa=
cility-to-continue-expansion-to-lending-20250507)

Defacto Scales Securitization Fund to =E2=82=AC300M with Citi and Viola Cr=
edit

At the intersection of working capital and private credit=2C Defacto =2C t=
he French API-based SME lender=2C  is expanding its securitization fund to=
 =E2=82=AC300M with Citi and Viola Credit as lenders. This new facility pr=
ovides Defacto with an annual funding capacity of up to =E2=82=AC1.8B=2C f=
ueling its continued growth.
Read More (https://www.linkedin.com/posts/getdefacto_300m-defacto-fct-stru=
ctured-like-a-tiramisu-activity-7351514216744271872-Wmi8?utm_source=3Dshar=
e&utm_medium=3Dmember_desktop&rcm=3DACoAACM8k1MBlKx7SWSOMhcbFG3LpPrvUbT-_q=
0)

Two Raises =E2=82=AC13M to Scale B2B Payments Platform

Oslo-based B2B payments platform Two has raised =E2=82=AC13M in a strategi=
c funding round=2C bringing its total funding to over =E2=82=AC40M. The ne=
w capital will support the company=E2=80=99s expansion into the US and key=
 Western European markets as it continues its mission to make B2B transact=
ions as seamless as consumer checkouts.
Read More (https://tech.eu/2025/07/11/two-raises-eur13m-to-scale-its-b2b-p=
ayments-solutions/)

Hokodo raises =E2=82=AC10M equity round led by Korelya Capital and Opera T=
ech Ventures to expand digital trade credit solutions across Europe

UK-based B2B lender Hokodo has raised =E2=82=AC10M in equity=2C in a round=
 co-led by Korelya Capital and Opera Tech Ventures (BNP Paribas=E2=80=99 v=
enture arm)=2C with participation from existing investors Mundi Ventures a=
nd Notion Capital.

The funding will support the expansion of Hokodo=E2=80=99s digital trade c=
redit offering=2C including a new in-store solution for offline and omnich=
annel B2B merchants across Europe.
Read More (https://www.hokodo.co/resources/hokodo-secures-eu10m-equity-rai=
se-led-by-korelya-capital-and-opera-tech-ventures-for-digital-trade-credit=
-product-innovation)

The United Kingdom-based consumer credit card lender Yonder has launched a=
 new debit card as it expands across Europe with a rewards program tailore=
d to Gen Z.
Read More (https://www.finextra.com/newsarticle/46226/yonder-launches-debi=
t-cards)


